                "style": "p",
                "content": "ith the aging population, the tremendous advancements in technology, and our demand for the best quality of life, the healthcare industry is facing a growing shortage of well-trained personnel. Throughout the North Americanhealthcare industry, there is an acute need to increase the size of the workforce and raise the skill level of that workforce."
            },
            {
                "style": "p",
                "content": "This program provides students with the basic knowledge, skills, and work experience neededto become permanently employable in a CSW and AW setting."
            },
            {
                "style": "p",
                "content": "well-trained Community Service and Addictions Worker (CSW) is equipped with a flexible, adaptable career. Social and community service workers administer and implementa variety of social assistance programs and community services specializing in addictions. They assist clients to address personal and social problems. They are employed by social service and government agencies, mental health agencies, group homes, shelters,substance abuse centres, school boards, correctional facilities, and other establishments"
            }
